# Hostname Map — sample/scaffold
# Source of truth: homelab DNS zone (vgriz.com internal domain).
# Promote to hostname-map.csv after review, then wire into Vector (Phase 2).
#
# Fields:
#   ip          - IPv4 address (exact match against src_ip / dst_ip)
#   hostname    - FQDN from internal BIND zone
#   short_name  - operator-friendly short label used in dashboard display
#   device_type - proxmox, truenas, kube-node, switch, gateway, dns, ap, vm, k8s-service
#   notes       - free text, not used by Vector
#
# Format guidance:
# - Kubernetes nodes (172.18.1.61-64) are already labeled via Wave 3b k8s enrichment
#   (src_k8s_node / dst_k8s_node). This map provides a fallback hostname for flows
#   where k8s enrichment does not fire. Dashboards should prefer src_k8s_node for
#   node-type flows.
# - MetalLB service IPs (172.18.1.201-230) are included for dst_ip label context.
# - DHCP clients and guest WiFi are not listed — they display as unknown-{ip}.
ip,hostname,short_name,device_type,notes
